draw((0,5)--(1,4),red,Arrow(6));

label("$\begin{pmatrix} a \\ 4 \end{pmatrix}$", (A + B)/2, N);
label("$x$", (8,0), E);
label("$y$", (0,8), N);
[/asy]

Then the line passes through $\begin{pmatrix} a \\ 4 \end{pmatrix}$ and $\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 5 \end{pmatrix},$ so the slope of the line is
\[\frac{4 - 5}{a - 0} = -1.\]Solving $a = \boxed{-1}.$

